notesStmt.note: Pasted in notes (flyleaf 1 recto) include collation of: a10 b8 c12 d6 e12 f10 g-u8 x2 - new collation reflects a change in f10 to f8 and in g-u8 to g-t8; Vellum of the binding has broken on the back of spine, in joints, and front cover

msIdentifier.collection: Hampton L. Carson Collection on the Growth and Development of the Common Law

msContents.summary: This manuscript contains Statuta vetera (Old Statutes).

msItem.title: Statuta de compositione moneta; Statuta de moneta

supportDesc.extent: i+170+i; 179 x 122 mm bound to 185 x 130 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil, lower right recto and upper right recto; contemporary foliation upper right recto

p.catchwords: Irregularly (folios have been trimmed), horizontal lower inner margin verso

layoutDesc.layout: Frame-ruled in lead in one column of variable lines ranging from twenty-six to thirty-two lines, prickings visible; running headings throughout; written area: 145 x 89 mm

decoDesc.decoNote: Illuminated initial (fol. 1r); red and blue initials decorated with pen flourishing and foliate designs throughout; paragraph marks in red and blue; marginalia and glossing throughout

binding.p: Late eighteenth-century tooled vellum binding. Two metal clasps. Stamped on spine: "INSPEXIMUS EDWARDI PRI[MUS] MAGNA CARTA ET ALLIS STATUTIBUS"

history.provenance: Hampton L. Carson, Philadelphia; given to the Free Library of Philadelphia in 1929; Book plate of the Free Library of Philadelphia, gift of Hampton L. Carson, pasted onto inside front cover. "M 1" written in ink and pasted onto inside front cover
